Yikes. Just got moderate food poisoning here. I should have seen it coming, but I was too damn hungry. I got the salmon benedict (which, side note, was served on a single large piece of toast instead of an English muffin. Lame.). The fish was lukewarm and a bit grainy. In retrospect I think it hadn't been stored properly. I was nauseous for about three hours.  My wife's meal was also subpar, but at least safe. Also, the service was mediocre and so I tipped 15%. Waiter chased us out of the restaurant and asked for an explanation. I felt bad for her but still found her reaction odd. It's not like I stiffed her.  But the one star is for poisoning me, not service or food quality.

I came here for evening drinks with a friend. it was pretty empty when we got here and we were seated immediately. As a nice touch for the outdoor space they have heating lamps up on the ceiling so you can still sit there and not feel really cold. It is shuttered as well. The whole space has a lot of wood, a long wooden tables with some benches at the end, the inside space has just regular tables and chairs. They also have a movie projector and a big white screen on which the project movies. The whole area has a reminiscence of a tiki bar with plants on the ceilings.  I had the bourbon cocktail with the plum jam, it was delicious and well prepared, my friend had the spicy margarita, and she really liked it as well. Service was good the wait staff doesn’t necessarily seem well trained but they are very helpful and definitely try and get you your information and orders quickly and correctly. They also come in to check on you without rushing you. We spent about three hours there and we didn’t feel like anyone was pushing us out of the door. Of course it might’ve been because it was a Monday night.  I definitely like this place and I'll be back

I met with a friend just this monday night. She had already been eating when I arrived. I decided to order a drink I had been sitting 10 minutes. Sophia the server comes over after I waved towards her. Rude but I didn’t want to wait so maybe that’s why she wasn’t pleasant. She gets me my drink and doesn’t come back to ask whether I wanted food. Fine. I wasn’t too interested in eating with my friend there. I was more interested in maybe coming back. I wave Sophia down again and ask for the check. Now why would she put the check together if I just got there? Fine once again but my friends bill came to 80 dollars leaving my ONE drink on there. She never offered to spilt the bill for me. My friend and I btw were not yet done with the drinks. My friend pays the bill. Sophia comes back “Well was there anything wrong with my service because you only left me a dollar tip.” Which she said loudly where she definitely had all eyes on us. She didn’t even wait for us to finish our drinks to leave the top. She definitely could of at least waited like a normal waitress. We weren’t press for time. My friend was a little drunk off of their amazing Froze drink hahaha. My star is definitely for the waitress. Her energy was not welcoming at all. Seems like a nice place but the staff needs improvement they all look like sorry ass workers. Thanks Sophia for a great first experience btw sorry on behalf of the drunk friend but if you serve alcohol you definitely need to be a little more friendly and understanding. Hospitality is definitely not for you. And because you were so unwelcoming I took time out my day to write this. I don’t think I would come back here. Service is everything.

Really enjoyed coming here with my 2 friends after an evening of eating at a nearby sushi spot. On a cold winter evening, walking inside felt like refuge from the cold elements. While the warmth provided immediate relief from the elements, we were struck by the interior decor and well suited music. The ambiance was on point.  We made our way to a table that looked like it would fit our scene, and we were greeted by our waitress. After receiving menus and water, each of us ordered a cocktail. I had the "Laundromat Fire" and it was out of this world. It brought me to another place. My friends enjoyed their drinks as well. The unexpected highlight was ordering the donuts. When they came out, they were hot and fresh, just made, and they arrived with a side of glaze.  We also spotted other people ordering late night meals, and everything looked tempting. Not giving into temptation, we ordered another round of donuts, and called it a night.  Great food, great drinks and fantastic service. Also the grafitti in the bathrooms is cool AF!

Beautiful place. Staff is friendly and service is at the ready. There’s a little bar inside and the music playing is good too. They even have board games for you to play while you wait for food. I’d suggest going during the warmer seasons. You’d get to truly enjoy the view of the outdoor dining area and the canopy of plants above you.

OK, Forrest Point is fun and decorated very well. The service is fine even though they accidently spilled a drink on me!. Had the cheeseburger and waffle fries. They were nice enough and sauteed my onions as requested. The burger was medium, and average at best. Considering all the rave reviews I wonder if people were under the influence of the libations. I did have a beer and a shot, but it didn't change my review of the burger. The vegan burger was average too, nothing special. That said I will have to go back and try some of the other offerings in an attempt to find what everyone is writing about. Till then, try it out and tell me what you think. Happy Holidays!
